divs: Sighting DetailsI shot this picture during my trip to Brussels in Belgium (see picture for location). It was a nice sunset so, I shot few pictures of it. When I look at them few days after, I saw this weird spot on the bottom left of one of the picture. I don't think this is a cloud because of the orientation, shape and it is a little brighter than the rest of the clouds around. I didn't see a plane, birds or any kind of activity in the sky at the moment I was taking the pictures. I took 6 pictures with an interval of 45 sec to 1 min (approx) and this weird thing appears only on the third picture. I show that picture to some friends and they couldn't give me an answer of what is this. I hope you can find something of this. Cheers.
